[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hibernian: Mark Oxley in talks with Southend United

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Hibernian goalkeeper Mark Oxley is in discussions with Southend United, BBC Scotland understands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Oxley has a year left on his contract with the Scottish Championship side, but has an option to leave in his deal.
Oxley, 25, made 46 appearances for the Hibees last season, but was usurped by Conrad Logan as the club failed to earn promotion, but lifted the Scottish Cup.
Hibs head coach Neil Lennon is understood to be seeking a new goalkeeper.
